---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '~/components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '~/components/Footer.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service — Nexigrate" description="The terms of service for using Nexigrate." pathname="/terms">
  <Nav />
  <main id="main" class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <p class="pill mb-5">Terms</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-900 sm:text-5xl">
      Terms of Service
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted-500">
      Effective date: 23 May 2026 · Governed by the laws of India.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 leading-relaxed text-ink-800">
      <p>
        These Terms govern your use of Nexigrate (the “Service”), available at
        <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="https://nexigrate.com">nexigrate.com</a>,
        <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="https://app.nexigrate.com">app.nexigrate.com</a>,
        and our APIs at <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="https://api.nexigrate.com">api.nexigrate.com</a>.
        By creating an account or by using the Service you agree to these Terms.
        If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">1. Who we are</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Nexigrate is operated by the Nexigrate team based in India
          (“we”, “us”, “our”). Until incorporation we operate as a sole
          proprietorship; once registered we will update this section with the
          legal entity name and CIN. You can reach us at
          <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="mailto:hello@nexigrate.com">hello@nexigrate.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">2. Eligibility</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Service is intended for students preparing for Indian school and
          competitive exams. Users under 18 may use the Service only with the
          consent of a parent or legal guardian. We may ask for verifiable
          parental consent before processing any data of a user we have reason
          to believe is a minor, in line with the Digital Personal Data
          Protection Act, 2023.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">3. Accounts and verification</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You sign in with a Google account or, when available, a phone-based
          one-time password. You are responsible for keeping your sign-in
          credentials secure and for all activity under your account. We may
          ask you to complete identity verification before granting access to
          paid plans or higher rate limits.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">4. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>resell, redistribute, or republish our content without permission;</li>
          <li>scrape, crawl, or otherwise extract content at scale;</li>
          <li>circumvent rate limits, paywalls, or anti-abuse controls;</li>
          <li>upload content that is illegal, defamatory, or violates the
              rights of others;</li>
          <li>use the Service to cheat in a real exam or to facilitate
              cheating by others;</li>
          <li>impersonate another person or misrepresent your affiliation.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">5. Subscriptions and payments</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Free use of the Service is subject to fair-use rate limits. Paid plans
          (Scholar, Aspirant, Achiever) are billed in Indian Rupees and processed
          by <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="https://razorpay.com">Razorpay</a>.
          We do not store full card numbers on our servers. Subscriptions
          continue for the period you paid for and do not auto-renew unless we
          announce it explicitly in advance. Refunds are governed by our
          <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="/refund">Refund Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">6. Educational content</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Multiple-choice questions, explanations, and study notes are derived
          from publicly available NCERT textbooks, previous-year question
          papers, and government-published syllabus materials, used under
          fair-use educational provisions with original publishers credited.
          AI-generated drafts are reviewed by human subject-matter experts
          before they are published in the daily MCQ stream. We do not
          guarantee that any specific question will appear in any specific
          exam.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">7. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Nexigrate name, logo, design system, code, and original copy on
          this site are owned by us. You retain ownership of anything you
          submit to the Service (notes, feedback, draft answers); you grant us
          a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free licence to use that content
          to operate and improve the Service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">8. Privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Our handling of personal data is described in the
          <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>,
          which is incorporated into these Terms by reference.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">9. Termination</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You may stop using the Service at any time and request deletion of
          your account by emailing us. We may suspend or terminate accounts
          that violate these Terms, after reasonable notice except in cases
          of clear abuse, fraud, or legal risk to us or other users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">10. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Service is provided on an “as-is” and “as-available” basis. While
          we work hard to keep content accurate, we cannot guarantee uptime,
          freedom from errors, or fitness for any specific exam. Use of the
          Service does not guarantee any particular score or outcome.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">11. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability to you
          for any claim arising out of or related to the Service is limited to
          the greater of (a) the amount you paid us in the twelve months
          preceding the event giving rise to the claim, or (b) ₹1,000. We are
          not liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
          punitive damages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">12. Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update these Terms from time to time. Material changes will
          be announced on this page and, where relevant, by email at least 7
          days before they take effect. Continued use after the effective date
          means you accept the updated Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">13. Governing law and disputes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any dispute that we
          can’t resolve by friendly conversation will be subject to the
          exclusive jurisdiction of the courts at Bengaluru, Karnataka.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-900">14. Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions, complaints, or DPDP grievances:
          <a class="text-ember-600 underline" href="mailto:hello@nexigrate.com">hello@nexigrate.com</a>.
          We aim to respond within 7 working days.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
